:49.031-0600","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/10001","description":"This issue has been validated/reproduced, but has not been prioritized yet.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Confirmed","id":"10001","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10014","id":"10014","name":"Storage Controller"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"As per attached support matrix, 3PAR allows 256 read-write and 2048 read-only virtual copies per virtual volume. Current 3PAR integration uses read-write virtual copies to represent EBS snapshots when <cluster>.storage.threeparoptimizesnaptovol is false. This limits the number of EBS snapshots that map to 3PAR read-write virtual copies to 256 per EBS volume. After this limit is hit, EBS snapshots for that specific EBS volume would have to be 3PAR physical copies (slower to create and less data efficient). \r\n\r\nOne way of increasing this limit is to employ read-only virtual copies to represent EBS snapshots. It does pose an issue which was the reason why it was not adopted earlier. The issue being physical copy can only be created from a base virtual volume or a read-write virtual copy, and not from a read-only virtual copy. Physical copy operation is necessary for creating EBS volume from the EBS snapshot. In order to work around this issue, euca-3PAR integration could create a read-write virtual copy from the read-only virtual copy on demand i.e. whenever a physical copy needs to be created. The read-write copy could be removed once the physical copy operation has completed.","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":nu